# Trivy ignore list for the contextmatrix-agent worker-image scan.
#
# The worker-image-scan job fails on CRITICAL/HIGH vulnerabilities that have an
# upstream fix (ignore-unfixed: true). Every entry must carry a justification;
# review on each worker-image / Go-dependency bump and delete entries whose fix
# has shipped. Dependabot (.github/dependabot.yml) tracks the underlying bumps.

# --- The bundled npm CLI ships tinyglobby -> picomatch 4.0.3
# (/usr/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/tinyglobby/node_modules/picomatch);
# 4.0.4 fixes the ReDoS. This is npm's own transitive dependency, so it clears
# only when an npm upgrade pulls in the fixed tinyglobby/picomatch — no Go
# change here affects it. The worker container is single-tenant and only parses
# globs it generates itself, so the ReDoS is not reachable from a prompt
# attacker.
CVE-2026-33671

# --- The agent binary embeds the Docker SDK (github.com/docker/docker
# v28.5.2+incompatible); CVE-2026-34040 is a Moby *daemon* authorization-bypass,
# fixed in v29.3.1. The agent uses only the Docker *client*, against a trusted
# local daemon, so the daemon-side authz path is not reachable — govulncheck
# (which is call-graph aware) reports no finding for it. The v28 -> v29 fix is a
# major SDK bump; Dependabot will raise it as a reviewable PR. Accepted until
# then.
CVE-2026-34040
